The paper discusses techniques for testing software, which is a topic that falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) category. The paper specifically focuses on combining symbolic execution and fuzzing, which are both techniques used in security testing (cs.CR) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also mentions the use of search-based heuristics, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper proposes new ideas for test-case generation, which could potentially involve machine learning (cs.LG).
